---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

In a #small pot{}, combine @white rice{1/2%cup}, @water{3/4%cup}, and a @salt{pinch}. Bring
to a boil, then cover and reduce to a simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, trim and halve @zucchini{1} lengthwise; cut crosswise into 1/2-inch-thick
half-moons. Drain @corn{1}; pat dry with #paper towels{}. Toss zucchini on a #baking sheet{}
with a large drizzle of @cooking oil, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until
browned and tender, ~{14-16%minutes}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @BBQ sauce{4%tbsp} and @mayonnaise{2%tbsp}. Add @?water{1%tsp}
at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

Open package of @diced skinless dark meat chicken{10%oz} and drain off any excess liquid.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil in a large  pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken
and corn in a single layer; season with @ranch spice{1%tbsp}. Cook, stirring occasionally,
until chicken is cooked through and corn is browned, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> TIP: If corn begins to pop, cover pan.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}.

Divide rice and zucchini between shallow #bowls{} in separate sections. Top rice with
chicken and corn; drizzle with as much sauce as you like. Serve with any remaining
sauce on the side.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.